ka and Santa Fe Railway | The Atchison, Topeka and Santa Fe Railway (reporting mark ATSF) , often referred to as the Santa Fe or AT&SF, was one of the larger railroads in the United States. Chartered in February 1859, the railroad reached the Kansas-Colorado border in 1873 and Pueblo, Colorado, in 1876. To create a demand for its services, the railroad set up real estate offices and sold farm land from the land grants that it was awarded by Congress. Despite the name, its main line never served Santa Fe, New Mexico, as the terrain was too difficult; the town ultimately was reached by a branch line from Lamy.'], 'question': 'Ironically, which city did the Santa Fe 1010 locomotive never travel to?', 'reasoning': 'The Santa Fe 1010 locomotive never traveled to Santa Fe, New Mexico, despite the name of the railroad suggesting otherwise.', 'answer': 'Santa Fe, New Mexico'}) (input_keys=None), Example({'augmented': True, 'context': ['Turner, Montana | Turner is a census-designated place and unincorporated community in Blaine County, Montana, United States. Turner is located on Montana State Highway 241 41.5 mi east-northeast of Chinook. Its population was 61 as of the 2010 census. Turner has a post office with ZIP code 59542; it also has an airport, Turner Airport. Turner is the farthest community in the continental U.S. from a Major League Baseball park; it lies 646.93 mi from Safeco Field in Seattle, the nearest park.', 'Turnersville, Texas | Turnersville is a town located in Coryell County, Texas approximately 40 mi west of Waco, Texas and approximately 12 mi north-northeast of Gatesville, Texas. The town sits approximately two miles southwest of the intersection of FM217 and FM182 at 31° 30\' 00"N, 097° 37\' 30"W The Middle Bosque River flows through the center of town while the Goldy\'s Branch flows just north of town. The two branches come together less than 1/2 mile east of the community and continue east southeast to Lake Waco.', 'Turner Airport | Turner Airport (